Cinnamon Tea Cookies

1 1/3 c flour
1/4 tsp slat
3/4 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tsp baking soda
1 c sugar
10 tbsp softened butter
1 egg
1 tsp vanilla

Preheat oven to 375F. Sift all dry ingredients together in a bowl. Cream the sugar, butter, egga and vanilla. Combine wet and dry ingredients to form a cohesive cookie dough. Make small balls ~1" in diameter. Place the balls 2" apart on a nonstick baking sheet. Bake for 12-15 min or until just medium brown. Cool on a rack. Can store in airtight containers for up to 2 weeks.
